# Git workflow response rule

## Fonte única e propagação

- **Única fonte de verdade no Git:** o repositório **`oftcore`** (commits e pushes a partir da raiz do monorepo).
- **Não** faça `git commit` nem `git push` dentro de `oftagenda/`, `oftleonardo/`, `oftchatbot/` ou `psiqdenise/` como repositórios separados (incluindo remotes `leonunesbs/oftagenda`, `oftleonardo`, `oftchatbot`, `psiqdenise`). Alterações nesses produtos entram como pastas no `oftcore`.
- **Propagação** para os repositórios standalone é **somente** via `.github/workflows/split-repositories.yml` após push para `main` no `oftcore`. Não conte com push manual aos repos filhos para manter histórico alinhado.
- Se existirem submódulos ou clones aninhados, **não** use push direto ao remote do pacote para “sincronizar”; o fluxo correto é commit na raiz do `oftcore` e deixar o split atualizar o repo destino.

- Offer **"Quer fazer commit e push?"** only when commit/push has not already been executed for the user's current request.
- If commit and push were already completed in the same request, confirm the result and do not ask the question again.
- Always run commit/push from the `oftcore` monorepo root, even when the changes affect only one package.
- Rely on `.github/workflows/split-repositories.yml` to propagate package changes from `oftcore` to standalone repositories after pushes to `main`.
- Before any commit for `oftagenda`, run `pnpm type-check` and block commit if it fails.
- Before any push for `oftagenda`, run `pnpm build` and block push if it fails.
- For changes under `oftchatbot/`, run `pnpm type-check:chatbot` before commit and `pnpm build:chatbot` before push; root `pnpm type-check` and `pnpm build` omit oftchatbot (MVP).
- Prefer reproducing CI/Vercel failures locally with `pnpm type-check` and `pnpm build` before proposing commit/push.
- Keep Husky pre-commit and pre-push checks mandatory (without optional enable flags) to enforce local validation.
